Tammy Petersen, News24Motorbike. (File, Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein - A bike without its driver crashed into a car on the N3 after the biker was &ldquo;catapulted&rdquo; to his death on the N3 near Harrismith on Sunday.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said paramedics responded to the scene where reports indicate that the biker had a blowout which saw him flung off the bike and into a tree and barriers.&ldquo;The motorbike continued down the road and collided with a car. The driver reports that he saw the bike hurtling towards him without a rider but was unable to avoid it,&rdquo; Botha said.Paramedics found the biker lying about forty metres from the twisted frame of the bike. &ldquo;Tragically he died on impact due to the extensive injuries that he sustained. The occupants from the car miraculously escaped uninjured,&rdquo; Botha said.Authorities are investigating. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.